{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox person | name = Giancarlo Prete | birth_date = {{birth date|1943|02|05}} | birth_place = [[Rome]], [[Italy]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2001|03|09|1943|02|05}} | death_place = Rome, Italy | death_cause = [[Brain tumor]] | occupation = [[Actor]], [[stuntman]] and [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbing director]] | spouse = Elizabeth Jacinto }}
'''Giancarlo Prete''' (5 February 1943 in [[Rome]], [[Italy]] – 9 March 2001, also in Rome, of a brain tumour) was an Italian actor.
After he worked in the [[Film|cinema]] as stuntman, Prete went to [[Alessandro Fersen]]'s acting school (where he later returned as a teacher) and began to act in many films and in television serials.
In the following years Prete worked as dubbing director and acted only in television productions.
He was married to Elizabeth Jacinto.
